;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
;; SHORTENED-BLOCK CANDIDATES — 2026-07-14
;; Recovery-013 phase 1 audit output.
;;
;; Method: for every chapter under ~/code/curator/scheme-books/
;; book-of-*, extract the prose body (unwrapped from any SLAT
;; wrapper), then search BOOK/A-branch, BOOK/B-main,
;; BOOK/D-remote for same-slug files (slug = filename minus
;; NN- prefix, -rN suffix, and extension). Compare word count.
;;
;; Findings summary:
;;
;;   TRUE candidates (same slug, no -rN):        0
;;   Revision-draft variants (-rN):              91
;;
;; ─── TRUE candidates ─────────────────────────────────────────
;; None. For every canonical chapter matched to a same-slug
;; preserved counterpart, the canonical is at least as long as
;; the preserved version — often longer. No shortening detected
;; in that dimension. No restore action needed from same-slug
;; comparisons.
;;
;; ─── Revision-draft variants ─────────────────────────────────
;; These are chapters where a preserved -rN (e.g. ch10-name-r1.md,
;; ch07-name-r2.md) contains materially MORE content than the
;; canonical chapter of the same slug. Two interpretations:
;;
;;   (a) The r-variant is an EARLIER expanded draft that got
;;       polished DOWN into canonical. In this case, canonical is
;;       correct — do not restore.
;;
;;   (b) The r-variant is a LATER expansion labeled with -rN for
;;       revision-track hygiene but never landed as canonical.
;;       In this case, its content should merge or replace.
;;
;; Spot-check of book-of-music/ch01-surface-of-sound-r1.md shows
;; interpretation (b) is plausible for at least SOME entries — the
;; r1 header reads 'refill r1 — more', suggesting it was authored
;; as additional-material to append to canonical, not a superseded
;; draft. Alfred must decide per chapter.
;;
;; RESTORE POLICY: NO WHOLESALE RESTORE APPLIED. All r-variants
;; remain preserved in BOOK/ (no deletes doctrine). Restoration
;; requires Alfred's per-chapter go/no-go.
;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

(shortened-block-audit
  :date "2026-07-14"
  :recovery-item "recovery-013"
  :phase "phase-1-audit"
  :true-candidates 0
  :revision-draft-candidates 91
